race.comment: KINGDOM UNDERSIEGE (6) went forward first-up and recorded a determined win over 1100m at Murwillumbah. He was heavily supported and has more to give. Draws awkwardly but has good gate speed. Suitably placed to repeat the dose. WINCHMAN (2) raced on the speed beaten 1.5 lengths over 1200m at Gold Coast. Is busting to win and this is a touch easier. Maps for the run of the race. DIZZY DEE (3) bounced straight to the front but emptied and weakened out over 1100m at Gold Coast. That was in tougher than this and she'd won her previous three starts all at Grafton. Will control the race and will be hard to peg back at this level. OCEAN DIVA (10) resumes and has switched from Sydney to the Matt Dunn yard. Will likely need it but is worth a market watch.
